itinerary.title: Musical Exploration in Ireland and Scotland
itinerary.content: Musical Exploration of Ireland and Scotland: It’s a trip of wild beauty, city bustle, historic icons – and 3 group performances! Start with Dublin’s St. Patrick Cathedral and Trinity’s Book of Kells. Ferry to Alloway and the port of Oban in Scotland’s Argyll area. Next, the isle of Iona, burial site of Scottish kings. Catch the Wallace Monument in medieval Stirling. Finish your tour in Edinburgh—a beautiful center for the arts.

itinerary.title: Middle School Honors Performance Series at Carnegie Hall
itinerary.content:
The Middle School Honors Performance Series at Carnegie Hall challenges elite students to perform at their very best. Students rehearse and perform under master conductors and have the opportunity to perform before invited representatives from collegiate and professional music programs. Though much of the students time is focused on performance preparation, the week also allows students to experience the best of the sights and the performance arts in New York City.

itinerary.title: Classical Highlights & Aegean Cruise
itinerary.content: Is there a better way to experience the island allure of the Aegean Sea than aboard a cruise? Prepare to be swept away by the unparalleled beauty and enchanting waters that surround Greece, Turkey, and Crete as you visit the top sights and perform in three locations – Mycenae & Corinth, Rhodes, and Athens. From ruins to realizations, trace the story of modern man on your 9 day tour of classical highlights and Aegean cruise.

itinerary.title: Music of Northern Italy
itinerary.content: Feel the magical allure of inspiration as your ensemble performs music in northern Italy and Rome. With an itinerary that features world-class sites – including the Roman Amphitheater, St. Mark’s Basilica, The Grand Canal, The Duomo, The Ponte Vecchio, remains of the Roman Empire, and much more – and performances in Venice, Florence, and Rome, your 11 day tour delivers a classic view of this remarkable part of the world.

itinerary.title: Rome to Salzburg
itinerary.content: Your journey from Rome to Salzburg is a tour of early civilization’s greatest city to the heart of the Renaissance and includes the home of one of the world’s most celebrated composers – Mozart. Your 12 day trip delivers enduring inspiration and incredible passion for the beauty of life – and music – including the ruins and holy landmarks of Rome, and abundant sights in Pisa, Cinque Terra, Venice, Munich, and more. Your performances cities are Rome, Florence, and Salzburg.

itinerary.title: Exploring Ancient Greece
itinerary.content: Exploring ancient Greece is to review the foundations of modern life, from mythology to political, scientific, and social standards adopted by countless countries across the globe. You’ll perform in three cities – Mycenae, Olympia, and Athens – taking in the vibrant scenery and mammoth-sized influence of Greek culture along the way. Your 9 day tour also includes visits to Eleusis, Nafplio, Delphi, and Cape Sounion.

itinerary.title: An Athenian Prelude
itinerary.content: Your Athenian prelude includes three concert performances in Athens, and your entire 9 day tour showcases the everlasting influence of Greek culture and mythology. Set your sights on Temple of Poseidon, The Acropolis, Temple of Olympian Zeus, and Museum of Popular Greek Instruments, as well as day trips to Mycenae & Corinth and Delphi. Feel centuries of history around you as you make your contribution of expression through performance.

itinerary.title: Paris & Madrid
itinerary.content: Paris & Madrid – two cities that hardly need an introduction. Start in The City of Light, where you’ll also perform, for tours that include revolution, art, architecture, and decadence. Move on to Madrid for your second performance and savor the royal display and bustling metropolis of Spain’s capitol, then move to Toledo for your third and final performance.

collection.title: Discover Washington, D.C.
collection.content: The best way to get a real appreciation for the history, the people, and the vision that have shaped our country is  a trip to the source. As our nation’s capital, this city brims with beautiful monuments, commemorative statues and memorials, and impressive national government centers, like the Capitol Building itself. Students of all ages flock to this special city for a face-to-face experience with our heritage. They come away with expanded appreciation and the memories of a lifetime.

collection.title: Theatre Performing Opportunities
collection.content:
When we think about a stage, we think about all of the players – cast, crew, writers, directors, audience – coming together to make a moment that is living right now. And that moment grows into a memory that has a life of its own – alive in the players that were all a part of it.

This is what our theatre performing opportunities are designed to create. It’s why we take you to new stages in epic places around the world – so you can be part of new, different moments that will endure. Moments that remind us how we got here and foretell where we’ll go.

collection.title: Dance and Cheer Programs
collection.content:
The stage is set. Your spotlight’s waiting.

Our popular dance and cheer programs give dancers and cheerleaders the chance to learn from star-quality professionals at high-exposure venues – like bowl games and national parades. Our dance and cheer travel programs give students one-on-one access to top-notch choreographers. No matter which you choose, your students will stretch, grow, and have some fun – under the lights and with friends in a fabulous new city. Our event choreographers are top names in the business, and they work with all skill levels. Come dance with Mandy Moore, Bonnie Story, or Travis Wall, to name a few!

collection.title: Other Professional Programs
collection.content:
In academic disciplines like law, engineering, medicine, education, and journalism, today’s students apply what they learn in a real world context. And that real world doesn’t end at the nation’s border.

Do you imagine education students exploring international standards? Nursing students working in a clinic in Central America?  Engineers meeting with the team constructing a skyscraper in a booming Asian capital? Our customized programs provide professional interactions that can help students in career-focused disciplines shape their future. Work with our Global Academic Team to craft a professional program that suits your curriculum. Before you start, explore our popular destinations to find the one that will inspire students in your field.

collection.title: Pre-Matriculation Adventure Programs
collection.content: Build excitement and community among your new cohort with travel programs to kick-off the full-time MBA or law school experience. For many universities, the pre-matriculation program has become integral to the class identity, bonding, and networking of students. Oftentimes, second-year students will serve as Program Leaders, working with WorldStrides to plan the logistics of the programs and recruit first-year students during the admissions process. We are proud to support these pre-matriculation adventure programs in destinations around the world, providing non-traditional networking opportunities for students outside the classroom.
